Peter Dada, Akure A drama ensued on Saturday night when the Ondo State Police Commissioner, Bolaji Salami, prevented the Deputy Governor, Agboola Ajayi, from leaving the State Government House in Akure, the state capital. It was gathered that Salami restrained Ajayi from leaving with his official vehicle. The development was not unconnected to the ongoing rift between the deputy governor and Governor Rotimi Akeredolu. It was learnt that the deputy governor is planning to dump the All Progressives Congress for another party due to the worsening relationship between himself and the governor. [READ ALSO] APC crisis: Amaechi, Abe’s factions clash as party replaces Giadom In a 41 seconds video that had gone viral, the CP was seen standing in front of the deputy governor, telling him he will not allow him (Ajayi) to leave the government house. “You have defected, your letter has been brought to my office,” the CP sternly said in the video. Ajayi then lashed back, “If I have defected, what is your own? CP, are you the chairman of APC? Are you the chairman of PDP? What is your concern if I defect? Details later…